from kbw kevin b weinrich subject summary how to make a window input be all cap thank to bruce barnett who recommend xvttool and bernward averwald and liam quin who recommend modify xdefault to get the desire behavior for a clas of xterm in xvttool simply create a key file that look like a a b b c c and specify say key file on the command line thi will translate any input into any other in my case lo-case to up-case work great and you get a customizable button-pad on the right or leave side to use an xterm solution add to ymy xdefault override key a string a n or override n key a insert-string a n key b insert-string b n and invoke a xterm name capxterm thank load kevin weinrich computer science corp kbw 